red around urban practices and people. The book uses drawings and photographs taken by the children themselves to trace the children’s journeys—lived and imagined—from their own perspectives, proposing an ethnographic analysis that recognizes children’s imaginations, play, and shifting desires as powerful catalysts of social change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Jun 2024) 0aChildrenzAmazon River RegionxSocial life and customs. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  alatin american, peru, indigenous, native, latino studies, latinx, amazon, amazon rainforest, matses, mayoruna, matsés, uncontacted people, uncontacted tribes, culture, childhood, adolescence, coming of age, sociology.1 aDësi, Roldán Dunú Tumi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishz978311131929208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishz978311131909408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023z978311131812708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023z978311079130340uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197882525340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978825253423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978825253/original  a978-3-11-079130-3  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131812-7  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023b2023  a978-3-11-131909-4  EBOOK PACKAGE Cultural and Area Studies 2023 Englishb2023  a978-3-11-131929-2  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023 Englishb2023  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGGb2